top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> Jenguss, I'm not forming a group of Lears to make a clique. When there are guild functions, we will not be in our groups, we will be with our entire family. Groups will be set up as the raid leader sees fit, not by what team you belong to.<br>
<br>
Even when it's not a guild raid, there will be many times when not everyone is available to be online. At those times, spots in the groups will be opened and filled by those needing groups that want to RvR with us. <br>
<br>
Lower levels in high level groups are ok, but the enemy goes after the ones that con lower to them all the time. Constantly forcing your group to try and rescue you from dead. Can be trouble, but something I'm willing to deal with if someone wants to come along to see the frontiers and RvR. <br>
<br>
 <p>Legar MacLear <br>
Steward of Siol Lear <br>
Troll Shaman</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=abbatoir>Abbatoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/28/01 6:49:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=193.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed Changes in Rank Structure and Meeting of the Si</span><hr size=1> I do not think that there is ever a need for concern regarding the unity of Lear, from top to bottom. There are some guilds out there that actually are already seeing the problem of folks staying only until 30, and then departing for other guilds. That will never be the case here, as this particular guild does have a great heart, and is a family first guild.<br>
<br>
What is needed is for folks to be vocal. Leadership in the guild benefits from that to no end. If ye think some mid level things would be a good thing? Post ideas for it! --- put events on the Calendar, and make it happen.. all thats needed is to have the initiative. If ye think that its' no good to post stuff on the boards, as the folks ye are hunting with are outside of the Guild - then invite them to the boards, and use it to leave messages with each other.. it's a public board my friend - and moreso, it's your home <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If any member wants to feel a part of things - they really just need to speak up for the most part and say hello is my experience. That's just the Lear way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Aye - ye might group more at tender levels with folks outside of the Guild - we all did.. and ye are going to see those same folks all the time! As they become realm ready, so will ye, so make your allies now my friend! Hopefully, you find yourself in groups with the same folks a lot, and get good grouping habits that way.. I hunted with Traxd, Miel, and Naraa for many seasons.. in time, they became Siol Lear as well, so it's great to be in the same guild now with the same group I grew up with.<br>
<br>
My experience also was that folks DID offer me a lot of respect for the name I had over my head ['cept for the shnooks!] <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#F2CF7E>- </font><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear>The Clan MacLear</a><font color=#F2CF7E> - </font><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9>The Great Hall of Midgard</a> <font color=#F2CF7E> - </font><a href="http://www.clanmaclear.com">The Clan MacLear Homepage</a><font color=#F2CF7E> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

